Author: jl777c#5810
Content: there is format 's', which is a string less than 256 bytes long

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but it all needs to be converted to hex so the oraclesdata just gets a hexstring blob

Content: Is the 'S' have principal differences over 's' except of length size?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: 'S' is for strings longer than 256 bytes

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: i need to know how many length bytes there will be in the hexstring

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: you need to put the little endian length first, then the exact number of chars for the string

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: also, oraclesinfo will show a batontxid, that should be the most recent (confirmed) data point. so it starts from there and goes backwards

Content: each data tx has the previous batontxid

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: yes, it creates a backwards linked list

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: oraclessamples traverses this list
